adviseScripts.text: Neon has such an explosive personality.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: She told me she only likes music with a *bang*.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: I'm just not sure how to satisfy her desire.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: Fire a gun.
Sing a song like "Firepower, O Firepower".
Fire a gun...?
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: Ah, I see! You mean I should imagine the flame shooting from the barrel of a gun,
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: and use that as my inspiration!
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: I knew you could help me, Conductor!
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: ... I'm sorry.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: I don't think there's anyone out there who would want to hear me sing. My voice just isn't strong enough.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: I help Julia practice so that she can give a powerful performance for Neon.
Fast music is like a raging wave.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: Calm music, by contrast, is like a placid lake.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: Which type of music are you in the mood for today?
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: Fast as a wave.
Calm as a lake.
I knew it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: I figured you would know how to ride the flow of the music, Conductor.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: That's why I knew you would want to hear something with a quick tempo.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: Really?
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: Judging by the way you walk, I'm surprised to hear you say that.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: I talk with Julia about music.
Anis told me not to wander around aimlessly like a lost spirit.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: But, I haven't been wandering around at all!
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: Could... could Anis have seen my soul wandering around without me knowing?
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: She means you should make yourself known when walking about.
I do think Anis has the power to see other people's souls.
Really?!
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: My footsteps already ring out above the gentle rustle of the breeze...
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: But next time, I'll try to walk a little louder.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: I never dreamed that Anis had such power!
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: I've finally found something worth learning from her...
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: other than how to squawk away in a high-pitched voice all day.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: I talk with Julia about Anis.
I want to perform for my mentor, Mustang.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: However, I don't know what kind of music to prepare.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: Calming music that unveils the true essence of art itself.
Buoyant and entertaining music that will liven up the room.
Yes! My mentor takes art very seriously.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: But I'm not sure if music's tranquility is what excites him.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: Yes! The one thing my mentor constantly talks about...
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: is entertainment!
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: In that case, I'll win him over with the passion of my playing.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: Thank you for your advice.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: I spend time with Julia talking about Mustang.
Conductor, whenever I see you, my heart starts beating faster.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: I feel as if I've experienced this before...
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: But... where?
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: Whenever you see tasty food?
Whenever you get musical inspiration?
Why would food make my heart beat faster?
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: Flavor is enjoyed with the tongue.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: The heart has nothing to do with it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: Oh! Oh! That's it!
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: Whenever a wave of musical inspiration washes over my body, my heart starts pounding. Just like it is now.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: Conductor, you are like music to me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: I have a pleasant time talking with Julia.
Conductor.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: When it's raining, what kind of music do you like to listen to?
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: Tearjerkers that can make me cry like the clouds.
Bold, emotional music that washes over me like a downpour.
Tears in the rain...
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: A wonderful match!
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: Music that washes over you like a downpour...
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: I think I'm feeling a burst of inspiration.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: I spend time with Julia thinking about rainy days.
Rapi is so good to me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: She often takes care of me when I stay in the Outpost.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: I want to repay her somehow...
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: What kind of music can best express my gratitude?
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: What about something other than music? Something tangible that she can use.
Something solemn that matches Rapi's style.
Something tangible? But this violin is the only thing I own...
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: I'm sorry! I'm very grateful for what she's done, but I can't give her this violin.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: Right. Solemn, but with a hint of warmth.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: That sort of music would be perfect for her.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: What a wonderful idea! I'll do exactly as you say.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: I talk with Julia about our memories of Rapi.
Sometimes, when I'm up on the surface,
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: I get so lonely. It's almost too much to take.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: When I feel this way, what should I do?
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: Use your music to express yourself.
Have a musical battle with the Raptures.
You're right... I abandoned the thing I love the most,
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: and then complain about how lonely I feel.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: You've given me a lot to think about.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: Raptures can play music, too?!
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: Even so, I must never use music for battle.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: My mentor taught me that music is not about competition.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: Julia and I talk about how to keep from being lonely up on the surface.
Conductor.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: When you think of your hometown, what kind of music comes to mind?
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: Music that's full of nostalgia, with a tinge of warmth.
Music that's cold and forlorn.
Really?
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: No wonder you're such a warm person, Conductor.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: I'd like to visit your hometown someday.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: That's exactly how I feel.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: Despite growing up in such a cold and desolate place, you're still such a kind person.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: You really are amazing, Conductor.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: I spend time with Julia talking about our hometowns.
Anis seems startled every time she sees me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: She always makes me forget what kind of music I wanted to play.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: I wonder what it could have been?
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: A marching song that instills bravery into even the most cowardly of soldiers.
A melancholy requiem that comforts the soul.
That's right!
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: I wanted to make that scaredy-cat Anis a little braver.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: Now I remember. Thank you!
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: No.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: That would only scare Anis even more.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: She's so easily frightened...
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: I play music with Julia while we both think about Anis.
Julia is performing as if deeply immersed in her music.
Let her be.
Announce your presence.
I waited until Julia was done with her performance.
Conductor? How long were you...
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: That was an amazing performance.
You waited until I was done with my performance!
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: Thank you for doing that.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: Sorry, I got too caught up in my playing.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: I'll try to be more aware of my surroundings from now on.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: I spend some time with Julia listening to her play.
Conductor, you don't look so good.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: If you feel like something is weighing down on you, listening to some music might help.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: Should I play something soothing for you?
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: Actually, I'd prefer something more upbeat. I want to beat my fatigue into submission.
You don't have to play anything.
Beat one's fatigue into submission.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: What an interesting notion!
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: I'll see what I can do.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: Are you sure?
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: Sometimes spending some quiet time alone can be the key to clearing your head.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: Rather than play anything, I'll just spend some quiet time together with you...
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: I spend time with Julia relaxing.
When you are resting, what kind of music do you listen to?
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: Music that gives me nice dreams.
I don't listen to music.
You mean to say that listening to music in real life
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: can influence your own dreams?
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: That's amazing!
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: I had no idea you weren't a fan of music...
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: I can't even imagine going through life like that.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: I try to pick out some music to listen to while hanging out with Julia.
There are so many different holidays and days of remembrance.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: If you could make today a holiday, what would you have it commemorate?
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: The moment where I stood and spoke with you about this very topic.
The moment I heard you play your music.
But then we'd have to talk about the same thing every year!
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: I like seeing you, but
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: that might get boring after a while...
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: So, that would mean
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: on this same day every year, I would be able to play for you.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: That would be fantastic!
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: Julia and I have a conversation about various holidays meant for commemoration.
A lot of people say you should ride a motorcycle at least once before you die.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: But I really don't think I'm the motorcycle-riding type.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: Is there anything else I could try riding?
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: You could ride the rhythm.
You could ride your violin.
Hey, that's right!
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: In a sense, I "ride" the rhythm everyday!
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: I can't believe I didn't think of that before.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: Um... I'm sorry Conductor, but
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: I can't be so careless with my violin!
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: It's much too precious to me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: I'll have to figure out something else.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: Julia and I try to figure out other alternatives to a motorcycle.
Conductor, so much has happened since I met you.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: My life and my music have both changed.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: I wonder how much more they'll change in the future?
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: Whatever the change ends up being, I'm sure it will be wonderful.
No matter how much things change, you'll always be who you are.
Thank you for saying such nice things.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: I too believe that any changes I experience will be for the better.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: You're right. No matter how much I change, I'll never not be me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: My love for music... and for you...
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: will always be with me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: Julia and I have a conversation about the passage of time and how things change.
Conductor, have you ever been to the Outer Rim?
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: I heard it's a sinister place filled with danger.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: Is that true?
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: More dangerous that you can even imagine.
It's a truly lonely and desolate place.
So the rumors are true.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: I was hoping there was another aspect to that place, so that I could get some musical inspiration from it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: Bummer.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: Ahah... I see...!
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: So there's a bit more to it then?
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: In that case, I'd love to go there someday for a little musical inspiration.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: Julia and I have a conversation about the Outer Rim.
Someone once told me that there's not a single performance that could satisfy every audience in the world.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: Sometimes, an audience just doesn't click with the performer.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: That got me thinking: Is there anyone that you just don't get along with?
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: Not in particular.
Oh, sure. Plenty of people.
I knew I could count on you, Conductor.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: To me, you're like a grand symphony. One that is all-encompassing,
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: comforting all those its notes reaches.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: So you're no exception...
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: I thought you would be...
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: I have a conversation with Julia about the relationship between an audience and the performer.
I had a nightmare last night.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: I had lost my violin and was wandering lost up on the surface.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: It was just awful! I can't get it out of my mind.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: But even in a nightmare, you never forgot how to play your music, right?
It's okay, it's not like you've lost your violin in real life.
That's right! Even though I had lost my violin,
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: I never lost my ability to play music.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: In a sense, that nightmare was actually a pathway for me to gain a new appreciation of music.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: Thank you, Conductor. I'm not scared anymore.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: You're right about that.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: My violin is safe and sound in real life.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: I'm sure I'll be fine. I just need some time.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: Thanks for your concern.
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: Julia and I talked about nightmares.
If you were to discover a legendary yet unprecedented music score on the surface,
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: what would you do with it?
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: I would have you perform it for me.
I'd pawn it for some quick cash.
You would trust me with such a precious composition?
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: You're too kind, Conductor!
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: Selling such a precious composition for money?!
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: That's inconceivable to me!
adviseScripts.speaker: Julia

adviseScripts.text: Julia and I talk more about what we would do with this legendary music score.
